&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Part Time 30 hours per week &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Neath Port Talbot Hospital has an exciting opportunity for an Allied Health Professional or Registered Nurse who has either completed the advanced practitioner qualification at BSC level or have completed 2 years of the MSc in Advanced Clinical Practitioner to join our Nurse Practitioner Team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you would like to be part of an established and innovative Advanced Nurse Practitioner Team working to continually develop and improve our expertise in caring for the frail older person. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be working alongside and collaboratively with the Ward Medical and Nursing Teams to provide high quality, evidenced based care for our patients. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/ or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Mrs. Ceri Thomas Lead Advanced Nurse Practitioner&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ceri.Thomas5@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
